      <p class="about-role">Senior Offensive Security Professional</p>
    </header>

    <div class="about-body">
      <p>
        I'm Kevin Suckiel — a security practitioner focused on offensive security, reverse engineering, and exploit development. I spend my time breaking things to understand how they work, and documenting the process so others can learn from it.
      </p>

      <p>
        This blog serves as a collection of my research, writeups, and technical deep-dives into topics ranging from CI/CD pipeline exploitation and ROP chain development to Linux system call tracing and web application vulnerabilities.
      </p>

      <h2>Focus Areas</h2>
      <p>
        Penetration testing, red team operations, reverse engineering, exploit development, cloud security, and CI/CD infrastructure attacks. I believe the best defenders are those who understand how attacks actually work — from initial access through domain compromise.
      </p>

      <h2>Philosophy</h2>
      <p>
        Anyone is capable of learning anything. Follow a methodology closely enough and you will be successful 90% of the time. But the real learning happens when you step outside your comfort zone and work through problems that are uniquely yours.
      </p>
